sentence: The Invesco S&P 500 ex-Rate Sensitive Low Volatility ETF ( XRLV ) is seeing unusually high volume in afternoon trading Monday, with over 136,000 shares traded versus three month average volume of about 43,000.
Shares of XRLV were up about 0.2% on the day.

Components of that ETF with the highest volume on Monday were Pfizer ( PFE ), trading up about 0.1% with over 11.2 million shares changing hands so far this session, and Exxon Mobil ( XOM ), up about 0.1% on volume of over 5.5 million shares.

Home Depot ( HD ) is the component faring the best Monday, higher by about 2.5% on the day, while Torchmark ( TMK ) is lagging other components of the Invesco S&P 500 ex-Rate Sensitive Low Volatility ETF, trading lower by about 4.6%.
